    <div class="about-lily-frame">
        <div class="about-lily-image-block">
            <p class="about-lily-text reveal">
                Lily's story
            </p>

            <img
                src="/images/LilyProtrait.PNG"
                alt="Lily"
                class="about-lily-image reveal reveal-delay-1" />

            <div class="about-lily-small-text reveal reveal-delay-2">
                <span class="eyebrow">From Gaza to a loving home</span>
                <br /><br />
                In the difficult days following October 7, Lily was found alone inside a house in Gaza that was
                expected to be destroyed. Her future was uncertain, but one soldier noticed her and chose not to leave her behind.
                He rescued Lily and brought her safely to Israel. That is where our paths crossed.
                <br /><br />
                We adopted her from the soldier and welcomed her into our family. At first, Lily needed time to understand
                that she was safe. Slowly, she began to trust, explore her new home, and show us her gentle and loving personality.
                <br /><br />
                Lily went from a place of fear and danger to a home filled with warmth, comfort and love.
                She discovered soft beds, peaceful naps, good food and people who cared for her deeply.
                <br /><br />
                Her story is more than a story of rescue. It's a reminder that even during the darkest times,
                a small act of compassion can save a life.
                <br /><br />
                This website was created to remember Lily's journey, celebrate the joy she brought
                into our lives, and share a story of hope.
            </div>

            <p class="about-lily-text about-lily-quote reveal reveal-delay-3">
                Sometimes, saving one small life may not
                change the whole world. But it changes the
                whole world for that one life.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
